        "con1": "Inactivity fees",
        "con2": "Strict identity verification",
        "con3": "Limited customer support"
      },
      "paypal": {
        "tagline": "The most known, but the most expensive",
        "pro1": "Widely accepted globally",
        "pro2": "Easy to use",
        "pro3": "Brand recognition",
        "con1": "Highest fees",
        "con2": "Occasional fund holds",
        "con3": "Unfavorable exchange rate"
      }
    },
    "faqTitle": "Frequently asked questions",
    "faqSubtitle": "Everything you need to know about international payments",
    "faq": {
      "q1": "What documentation do I need to receive international payments?",
      "a1": "You typically need official identification (passport or national ID), proof of address, and depending on the platform, your tax ID number. Some platforms may require additional documentation to comply with anti-money laundering regulations (KYC).",
      "q2": "How do taxes affect my international payments?",
      "a2": "International payments may be subject to taxes in your country. We recommend consulting with an accountant to understand your obligations based on your tax situation.",
      "q3": "What is the fastest way to receive payments?",
      "a3": "Wise and Skrill usually process in 1-2 business days. PayPal can be faster for initial deposits, but withdrawals to bank accounts take longer. If you need the money quickly, Payoneer and Skrill offer debit cards to use the funds immediately.",
      "q4": "How can I reduce fees?",
      "a4": "Some strategies: use Wise for large transfers (the percentage fee is the lowest), consolidate small payments into larger transfers so the fixed withdrawal cost has less impact, and talk with your clients about using platforms with lower sending costs.",
      "q5": "Can I have accounts on multiple platforms at the same time?",
      "a5": "Yes, and it's recommended. Many freelancers use Wise for European clients (for the exchange rate), Payoneer for marketplaces like Upwork or Fiverr, and PayPal as a backup option for clients who don't use other platforms."
    }
  },
